data.enText: a picture or pattern that is made by weaving coloured wool onto heavy cloth; the art of doing this

data.chText: 诸如刺绣和织锦之类的手工艺
data.enText: crafts such as embroidery and tapestry

word_means: 在一块挂毯中制织出或描绘

means: 在一块挂毯中制织出或描绘

tr: a wall hanging of heavy handwoven fabric with pictorial designs
a heavy textile with a woven design
something that resembles a tapestry in its complex pictorial designs

value.def: A tapestry is a large piece of heavy cloth with a picture sewn on it using coloured threads.

example.ex: The seats of the chairs had been recovered in tapestry...
He sat on a tapestry cushion next to the hearth...
example.tran: 他坐在壁炉边上的一块绣花软垫上。

example.ex: On the opposite wall is a large tapestry.
example.tran: 对面的墙上挂着一块大壁毯。

value.def: You can refer to something as a tapestry when it is made up of many varied types of people or things.

example.ex: Hedgerows and meadows are thick with a tapestry of wild flowers.
example.tran: 灌木树篱和草地中开满了五彩缤纷的野花。
芝加哥政坛的丰富多彩
